# Agent workflow

## Rejected work is permanent until the user reopens it

- If the user calls work **poison**, **dog shit**, or asks to **remove completely**, treat it as **rejected**.
- Do **not** re-implement rejected approaches in later turns — including when an old plan file is attached again.
- Before coding from an attached plan, scan the conversation for rejections and superseding instructions.

## Help only when asked

- Do not proactively implement, refactor, or "fix forward" unless the user explicitly requests implementation.
- Questions and reviews get answers only — no drive-by code changes.

## Visual / hero / atmosphere work

- Default mode: **Plan first** → user approves → then implement.
- Default surface for atmosphere experiments: **Storybook fixtures** (`stories/ui-evaluation/`, `components/portal-atmosphere/fixtures/`).
- Do **not** wire experimental hero/atmosphere layouts into production auth routes unless the user explicitly asks — **except** the approved Guardian Auth shell on `/auth/*` ([ADR-Auth-UI-001](docs/architecture/adr/ADR-Auth-UI-001-guardian-shell-neon-form.md), Method B).

## Quality bar before shipping UI

- Name the **reference PNG** and **layout zones** (editorial | owl | access card) before writing CSS.
- If the approach is a shortcut (one asset + filters, paste PNG, invert hack), **stop and plan** — do not ship.
- See `docs/architecture/slices/portal-atmosphere/pa-rejected-approaches.md` for banned patterns.
